The paper deals with worst case time bounds for NP-complete problems and proposes algorithms based on constraint satisfaction formulations. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of data structures (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational complexity (cs.CC), computational geometry (cs.CG), or machine learning (cs.LG). However, since the paper focuses on algorithmic techniques and worst case analysis, it is more likely to belong to the categories of data structures, computational complexity, or computational geometry.
